Workshops on networking etiquette begin in the adjoining classroom, and an alumni panel discusses how to prepare for technical interviews. Career counselors redirect unsure students toward applicable industries. Tech companies display demo screens showing their latest apps, and the engineering society sponsors a resume review table near the stage. Students use tablets at kiosks to upload resumes to the fair database, and small groups analyze which recruiters seemed most enthusiastic. Some students rehearse elevator pitches quietly against the wall. As the day winds down, interview sign-up sheets fill with names. Students exit with tote bags and a stack of business cards.

Recruiters distribute tote bags containing branded notebooks and pens, reminding students to follow up with personalized emails, and students exit with these tote bags and a stack of business cards. Event staff manage the entrance by scanning registrations and handing out lanyards, while career center staff log attendance metrics on laptops. Near the exit, a post-event survey link flashes on the monitors. In a separate area, healthcare providers showcase community outreach photos, and a cybersecurity company runs a password cracking challenge on a laptop. Additionally, some students rehearse elevator pitches quietly against the wall.
